<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../manrev.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>fr</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>pol2des  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>April 1993  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="pol2des"> conversion matrice de polynômes vers forme descripteur  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[N,B,C]=pol2des(Ds)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>Ds  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
  <SP>
    : matrice de polynômes
</SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>N, B, C  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
  <SP>
    : 3 matrices réelles
</SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    Etant donnée la matrice de polynômes <VERB>Ds=D_0 +D_1 s +D_2 s^2 +... +D_k s^k</VERB>,
    <VERB>pol2des</VERB> renvoie 3 matrices <VERB>N, B, C</VERB>, avec <VERB>N</VERB> nilpotente 
    telles que :
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>Ds = C (s*N-eye())^-1 B </VERB>
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
s=poly(0,'s');
G=[1,s;1+s^2,3*s^3];[N,B,C]=pol2des(G);
G1=clean(C*inv(s*N-eye())*B),G2=numer(G1)
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
